				<div class="content">
					<div id="post_message_1622889">
						<blockquote class="postcontent restore ">
							Ravenloft was really cool! <img src="images/smilies/smile.gif" border="0" alt="" title="Smilie" class="inlineimg" /> also Clyde Caldwell did *fantastic* art for the covers!<br />
only problem was, TSR went nuts, and did same thing to Planescape and Dark Sun: they forced the setting to change according to novels and a &quot;metaplot&quot;...<br />
<br />
so, Ravenloft got expanded and torn to bits and trashed, GRRRR!! (The GRand Conjunction etc), they kept bringing out more stuff for it, changing it each version. <br />
<br />
Planescape  I adored the &quot;factions&quot; and the way philosophy, what/how storng you believed was *THE* thing, not levels, items etc. Awesome!<br />
then you had the &quot;Blood War&quot;, adored the idea that law and chaos of evil were tearing into each other more than anything else (makes sense ot me,  &quot;law&quot; and &quot;chaos&quot; as oh, &quot;powers&quot; and beliefs as vital, needed and real to critters as good/evil, or food, wealth etc)<br />
The &quot;factions&quot; in Sigil represented various philosophical beliefs, not gods, but philosophical outlooks. Brilliant!<br />
And then they trashed it with the &quot;Faction War&quot;...wtf<br />
<br />
Dark Sun was awesome, then they killed half the sorceror kings (with some gimp NPCs, an 8th lvl gladiator kills Kalak? GTF! grr and the novels..omg the stupid stuff...<br />
<br />
So TSR wrecked three great settings...hence I ignore that crap they did back then: <br />
Kalak still lives, the history of Athas is completely unknown/different in my games, the Faction War never happened in Sigil, and Ravenloft is still as it was in 1st set! <img src="images/smilies/wink.gif" border="0" alt="" title="Wink" class="inlineimg" /><br />
<br />
<br />
Temple of elemental Evil is probably gonna be out for 4th ed (the Temple's mentioned in several places)<br />
Against the Giants is a 4th ed &quot;super module&quot; <img src="images/smilies/wink.gif" border="0" alt="" title="Wink" class="inlineimg" /><br />
<br />
Pool of Radiance, ah I loved it when you cleaved those bloody kobolds with one hit and had umpteen death cries, muhaha!<br />
<br />
One I forgot was Tower of DOom, the D&amp;D arcade game! damn that was good, &quot;Sticks ot Snakes&quot; was awesome! <img src="images/smilies/tongue.gif" border="0" alt="" title="Stick Out Tongue" class="inlineimg" /><br />
<br />
also fogot BALDURS GATE!m playing it at moment, brought up a hug enostalgi arish, hence the original post <img src="images/smilies/wink.gif" border="0" alt="" title="Wink" class="inlineimg" /><br />
Baldurs gate got me onto the net, the forum for it was crazy fun <img src="images/smilies/tongue.gif" border="0" alt="" title="Stick Out Tongue" class="inlineimg" /><br />
