			<div class="postrow has_after_content">
				
				
				<h2 class="title icon icon0">
					Re: Fave items/books from D&amp;D? :)
				</h2>
				

						
						
				<div class="content">
					<div id="post_message_1622948">
						<blockquote class="postcontent restore ">
							You all suck. Planescape was clearly the best thing they ever released!<br />
<br />
In particular, Faces of Evil: The Fiends was probably the best product they ever released. It was a D&amp;D book that didn't have a single new rule or stat in it. The entire book was just background, history, motivations and concepts for the three main fiendish races. How to play one as a DM, how to get across their ethos and philosophy, how they fight in combat - everything. It brought to life the demons that have plagued adventures since day 1 of DnD in a way no other product ever has done, and as a DM it was a fantastic resource for really bringing an adventure to life. <br />
<br />
My players loved it as well, because after that book their enemies became a whole ot more interesting. Just goes to show you don't need extra spells or weapons or massive maps to make a good adventure. It was easily the most &quot;roleplaying&quot; supplement TSR ever did.<br />
<br />
EDIT: Mother of gods my Planescape collection is worth a fortune according to Amazon. How on earth did that happen?
						</blockquote>
					</div>

					
				</div>
			</div>
			
