Maledict<br />
yeah, I didn't like the 2nd Dark Sun boxed set and way they changed it all, so didn't buy it, but it goes for like £100 freakin' quid now!<br />
agreed as a DM I adore good books of lore <img src="images/smilies/smile.gif" border="0" alt="" title="Smilie" class="inlineimg" /><br />
try &quot;The Illithiad&quot; if you cna find it, it's superb. they also did &quot;The Sea Devils&quot; and &quot;I, Tyrant&quot; at same itme in same vein for sahuaghin and beholders.<br />
<br />
I got put off Planescape by DeTerilzzi's art, OMG I can't stand his &quot;concentration camp escapee water colour&quot; stuff <img src="images/smilies/tongue.gif" border="0" alt="" title="Stick Out Tongue" class="inlineimg" /><br />
but love, as said, the idea of philosophy and &quot;will power&quot; being THE thing in the Planes, makes sense ot me <img src="images/smilies/smile.gif" border="0" alt="" title="Smilie" class="inlineimg" /><br />
I wanted to get the BLood War boxed set back then but couldn't afford it, now, its like £70+ on ebay!<br />
<br />
I had often run &quot;leaders&quot; as combat whimps, just <i>skills </i>etc that made 'em leaders, I liked how 3rd ed created the Expert and Aristocrat classes which was really good for such folk. And in 4th ed I can just say they have Skills and defences of &quot;x&quot; and whatever I want to make them a wee bit survivable but mostly useless in combat, though they might have tricks ot evade harm, like the &quot;demagogue&quot; template (a minion takes a hit for them), or have ability to charm by sheer willpower/psychiology etc<br />
<br />
I mostly liek the 4th ed changes, but the Blood War should NOT be &quot;On hold&quot;, quieter, sure, to allow PCs reaosnable chance to deal with each side but no way in hell (lol) there'd be a truce. simpel fact that the leaders can't control all their udnerlings etc would keep it going<br />
devils want power, s would exploit, trigger attacks etc<br />
demons lust for destruction and are chaotic so they'd attack anyway out of sheer hate<br />
<br />
also don't liek how 4th ed took out some alignments, that was *dumb* I liek alignments, it does work well as a simple, basic explanation of moral and ethical behaviour/outlook. it's only very &quot;hard coded&quot; in some critters like the Fiends, modrons etc<br />
if you write &quot;LN&quot; as a NPCs alignment, that is a super shorthand for the DM to know the likely behaviour!<br />
saves writing out screeds of stuff, as long as you remember it's the *typical* mindset, not absolute.
