				<h2 class="title icon icon0">
					Re: Fave items/books from D&amp;D? :)
				</h2>
				

						
						
				<div class="content">
					<div id="post_message_1623025">
						<blockquote class="postcontent restore ">
							For just Reading:<br />
<br />
<br />
<b>Deities and Demigods.</b>  When I was young it was like putting every Mythos ever in one book to be able to compare who was the toughest.  Made me go read Cthulu stuff and Elric stuff and Fhfard and the Grey Mouser stuff.   <br />
<br />
More recently <b>Ptolus</b>: <a href="http://www.montecook.com/cgi-bin/page.cgi?mpress_Ptolus" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">http://www.montecook.com/cgi-bin/page.cgi?mpress_Ptolus</a>  Wonderful place and a book I keep by my bed for when I cannot sleep and need something to read.  Wonderful world develoment.  I would play any game they ever made set there.<br />
<br />
For playing:  <b>Dave Arneson's Blackmoor.</b>  I loved the setting and the later adventures were all great.  If you want to get the flavor of this sort of obscure work go here and take a look at the docs: --- ugh edit... nevermind... looks like all the docs are gone... take my word for it... great high fantasy setting.
						</blockquote>
					</div>

					
				</div>
			</div>
			
